There are some codes you use as your password today that makes it easier for fraudsters to get access to your account.
Why do you think bank accounts tiday are easily hacked?? Its because of the weak codes we use as our password.
Without this four digit pin, you can’t make any transfers, withdrawals or other important transactions. I’ll advice you use a very strong code for your password to avoid being a victim.
Today in this article I’ll be showing you at least 12 codes you shouldn’t use as your password.
Below are codes you shouldn’t use
1. Don’t use years as your pin
1999
2003
2020
1887
2. Don’t use numbers in ascending or descending order
1234
7890
4567
9876
3. Don’t use the same numbers as your pin
5555
9999
7777
1111
I hope you found this article helpful. If you used any of these codes as your password please kindly go to your bank and change it.


